#compdef semcheck
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# semcheck — LLM-driven semantic checker (impl vs spec) (Go, 113★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/rejot-dev/semcheck
# org    : rejot-dev
# license: MIT
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from cmd/cli/cli.go
# on the semcheck tip — stdlib `flag` package var block + showUsage().
#
# Direct deps from go.mod:
#   github.com/yuin/goldmark v1.7.13           ← canonical Go CommonMark parser
#   github.com/charmbracelet/lipgloss          (terminal styling)
#   github.com/charmbracelet/log               (structured logging)
#
# semcheck parses Markdown / RFC-text specifications via goldmark to extract
# spec sections, then sends impl-vs-spec deltas to OpenAI / Anthropic / Gemini /
# Cerebras / Ollama models for semantic comparison.  Spec link syntax:
#   `semcheck:file(./local/spec.md)`
#   `semcheck:url(https://example.com/docs/api)`
#   `semcheck:rfc(8259)`              (auto-resolves to rfc-editor.org)
#
# === AXIS 154 CONTINUES — CommonMark / Markdown parser ecosystem ===
# Axis position: Go=209 continues Axis 154 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# CommonMark parser is `yuin/goldmark` by Yusuke Inuzuka — an extensible
# parser used by Hugo (largest static site generator), gohugoio docs,
# golang.org/x/website, gitea wiki rendering, soft-serve, and basically
# every Go markdown processor in production.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=209   _mdvi                ← previous round (axis 154 OPENS at 1/0/0)
#   Go=209     ← THIS FILE          (axis 154 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=209 ← next round        (axis 154 CLOSES at triple-209, slot 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_semcheck() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '-config=[path to configuration file (default semcheck.yaml)]:config file:_files -g "*.(yaml|yml)"' \
        '-help[show help message]' \
        '-version[show version]' \
        '-show-config[print full configuration]' \
        '-hide-analysis[hide additional analysis in results]' \
        '-pre-commit[run semcheck on staged files]' \
        '-init[create a semcheck.yaml file interactively]' \
        '-github-output[output GitHub Actions annotations]' \
        '-log-level=[set log level]:level:(info debug error warning)' \
        '*:files to check (specifications or implementations):_files'
}

_semcheck "$@"
